s directly behind.";i:24;s:73:"Then move your front foot behind the back foot before bringing them both.";i:25;s:67:"A woman can pick up a chair in each hand and walk around with them.";i:26;s:22:"We do it all the time.";i:27;s:100:"Put your hand down over the chair back and either grip the seat or the lower edge of the chair back.";i:28;s:65:"Best idea though is to look helpless and let a man come and help.";i:29;s:95:"Yes and its honestly quite satisfying to write as my physics teacher explained this quite well.";i:30;s:111:"This experiment has nothing to do with holding the chair but entirely with standing with your back on the wall.";i:31;s:58:"See when you hold the chair at an angle like that you are.";i:32;s:36:"Home chair lift challenge explained.";i:33;s:53:"2347 Chair Lift Challenge Explained Written By Admin.";i:34;s:28:"Saturday 25 April 2020 Edit.";i:35;s:65:"Tech On The Slopes How Rfid Is Changing The Experience Of Skiing.";i:36;s:50:"Finger Lift Challenge Original Impossible Youtube.";i:37;s:42:"Patient Lifting Equipment Market Size And.";i:38;s:65:"The lever arm for the couple is just half the width of your palm.";i:39;s:121:"This means you need to be able to supply a force much stroger than the weight of the chair to lift it and hold it steady.";i:40;s:155:"It is easier to lift from the back legs the com is closer to the back than the front and easier if you first tip the chair until the com is over your hand.";i:41;s:62:"Bend over the chair creating a 90-degree angle with your body.";i:42;s:33:"Place your head against the wall.";i:43;s:75:"Now try to lift the chair while keeping your head pressed against the wall.";i:44;s:45:"Results of this challenge may vary by gender.";i:45;s:96:"Interestingly enough many girls can successfully complete this challenge while most boys cannot.";i:46;s:39:"Again its all about the center of mass.";i:47;s:62:"Its about the chair challenge better known as chair challenge.";i:48;s:41:"This challenge consists of the foll